This paper deals with parity games, which are a central topic in both logic and game theory. The paper discusses equivalence relations that can be used to reduce the size of parity games, which is a common problem in model checking and satisfiability checking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses game-based characterizations of these relations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses coinductive characterizations of direct- and delayed simulation equivalence, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the winning regions of parity games, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
